race.comment: BUSH BOUQUET (1) had won two in a row before finishing third (25.51) last time at this track. Form at the trip sound including four wins. The form from her last run stacks up well. Top chance in this line up. RED HOT PENNY (8) shapes well for this after winning last start over 390m at this track in a lightning 21.47. Rates a leading chance if runs up to latest. NOAKI RADAR (2) has a strong winning strike-rate here having won two of four starts. Missed the frame latest (20.02) when fourth over 352m at this track in a Grade 4/5. Makes strong appeal on best. KALI (5) was well fancied last time on the strength of a win two back but could only manage seventh (19.20) at Q Straight.
